<item>
            <title>[SOLR-794] ClientUtils.escapeQueryChars escapes chars a bit aggressive</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-794</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This was talked before at:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nabble.com/ClientUtils-escape-query-td18833559.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.nabble.com/ClientUtils-escape-query-td18833559.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
I didn&apos;t notice it at that time though.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This method outputs weird string when Japanese letters are given for example. &quot;J1J2J3J4J5&quot; =&amp;gt; &quot;\J1\J2\J3\J4\J5&quot; We don&apos;t want to see it.&lt;br/&gt;
It should use QueryParser.escape() code as it says in javadoc.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
